● Here's what changed and why each decision was made:

  Card structure — padding: 0 on the card itself, with each zone (header,
  actions, rating, review) owning its own padding. This lets the border-bottom
  dividers run edge-to-edge cleanly instead of being inset.

  Hover effect — translateY(-5px) scale(1.01) combines a lift with a very subtle
   scale. The scale makes the card feel like it's coming toward you rather than
  just floating up. border-color also lightens slightly to reinforce the
  "selected" feel.

  .card-header — groups title and genre badge together with a border-bottom
  separator. The title jumps to 1.1rem / 800 weight with tighter letter-spacing
  for a more cinematic feel.

  Genre badge — switched from a hard border to rgba background and border so it
  reads as a soft tag rather than a UI control. The pill shape (border-radius: 
  20px) distinguishes it visually from the rectangular buttons.

  .card-actions row — flex: 1 on .btn-watched makes it fill available space
  while the favorite button stays compact at a fixed size. Both get matching
  border-radius: 8px and border styling so they look like a cohesive set.

  .card-rating separator — border-top: 1px solid #1e1e30 (slightly lighter than
  the card background) gives the star row a subtle divider without drawing too
  much attention. Using a slightly different color than .card-header's border
  creates visual hierarchy — the header separation is stronger than the internal
   ones.

  Review focus ring — box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(233, 69, 96, 0.12) adds a soft
  red glow on focus that matches the accent color without being harsh.

