  of a custom class — this keeps the visual state in sync with the accessibility
   attribute already being set by the JS, with no extra logic
  - Active state gets a red glow ring + dark red-tinted background so it clearly
   reads as "selected" independent of the emoji (useful if the emoji doesn't
  render)
  - The scale transform is moved to [aria-pressed="true"]:hover only — an
  already-favorited card bounces when you hover it; an unfavorited card does not

  .star:not(.filled)
  - The previous opacity: 0.25 on a dark background made the ☆ character nearly
  invisible
  - ☆ is a plain Unicode character, not an emoji — it inherits color directly,
  so setting color: #5a5a88 (a mid-tone purple-gray) makes it clearly visible
  without looking "active"
  - opacity: 1 overrides the old rule so the color takes full effect

  .star.filled
  - Added a drop-shadow filter with a warm yellow glow — this makes filled stars
   pop off the dark background and look distinctly "on"

