● What changed and why:

  Two different active colors — status filters (All / Watched / Favorites) use
  the red accent #e94560 since they represent primary navigation. Genre filters
  use a softer purple tint since they're secondary, refinement-level filters.
  Using the same active color for both would make it harder to tell which filter
   group is doing what at a glance.

  #filter-bar gets a container background — the three status chips now sit
  inside a pill-shaped tray (#13131f with a border). This groups them visually
  as "one control" rather than three floating buttons. The genre bar stays
  open/frameless because it has a variable number of items and a tray would look
   uneven.

  .filter-btn resting state uses background: transparent — since the buttons sit
   inside the tray, the tray itself provides the visual container. Individual
  button backgrounds in the resting state would create a box-in-box effect.

  .genre-btn keeps its own background: #1a1a2e border — without the tray
  container, genre chips need their own visible boundary at rest so they read as
   clickable.

  active:hover rules — both active states have a darker hover variant so the
  button still responds to hover even when selected, confirming it's still
  interactive (e.g. clickable to deselect in a future update).

  white-space: nowrap — prevents a genre name like "Sci-Fi" from breaking
  mid-word when the bar wraps on small screens. Chips wrap as whole units
  instead.

