● Here's what was polished and why:

  Font — Inter added at the top of the stack with -webkit-font-smoothing: 
  antialiased. Inter is purpose-built for UI at small sizes — it has better
  number rendering for the stats values and tighter letter-spacing than Segoe
  UI.

  clamp() on the header title — clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem) makes the logo scale
  fluidly between small and large screens instead of snapping at a breakpoint.
  On a 320px phone it shrinks gracefully; on a wide desktop it grows to 3rem.

  Two breakpoints instead of one — the old single 600px breakpoint was too
  blunt. Now:
  - 768px — tightens padding and adjusts the card grid minimum to 200px so two
  cards still fit on tablets
  - 480px — single-column cards, compact stat cards, reduced inner padding on
  card sections

  Stats cards on mobile — rather than stacking to 1fr (three tall cards), they
  stay repeat(3, 1fr) with reduced padding and smaller text. Three stats
  side-by-side at compact size reads better than a vertical list of three big
  cards.

  Card inner padding on mobile — .card-header, .card-actions, .card-rating, and
  .review-section all reduce their horizontal padding from 1.25rem to 1rem on
  small screens so text doesn't feel cramped inside narrow cards.

  Line height — bumped body line-height from 1.5 to 1.6 — a small change that
  makes the review textarea and card descriptions feel airier without affecting
  layout.

