  the flex container, separating it from the filter chips visually. No wrapper
  div or absolute positioning needed.

  Muted default, red on hover — at rest, the button is barely visible (#44445a)
  so it doesn't compete with the active filter chip. On hover it reveals red,
  signaling "this will clear something" without being alarming when you're just
  browsing.

  Reset button inside #filter-bar, not alongside it — the button is part of the
  filter system, so it belongs in the same container. Placing it outside would
  require an extra wrapper and make the layout more fragile on smaller screens
  where the bar wraps.

  e.target.closest("#btn-reset-filters") checked first — since the reset button
  is inside #filter-bar, the delegated filter listener would otherwise also
  process the click. The early-return guard prevents that without removing the
  button from the bar.

